K listen, I love drake and all but wtf is this!?!?
And ppl r commenting "this is the making out of the hood track"
U serious bro?!?
Drake has the potential to make instant hits, but this ain't one of em, period!
Drake; love u and all bro, but what is this!?
Like maybe you're trying to explore a new sound and new flavor to your tracks but shit, I'm just not feeling it!

Secondly: drake doesn't know ANYTHING about 'the hood' or what it's like to live anything but a lavish lifestyle. He grew up in the upper middle class. He never had to want or need for anything!
Now I'm not one to talk, I also grew up upper middle class in Burlington, on! K, so my fam had money but I also had NOTHING handed to me and worked my ass off for everything I wanted and strived for, just like drake. So what I'm saying is although he's fat from 'hood'
He worked his fucking ass off to make something out of himself and that I have mad respect for!
But regardless of how I grew up, I've been on the streets homeless, living in some trash shit hood apartment and it's nothing to be proud of. It's a fucking DISGUSTING horrible way to live with retarded crack head neighbours and fucking meth heads yelling and screaming outside your apartment complex all night and shit. God, I'd rather die then EVER go back to the few years I lived in poverty!
So I don't get how some ppl seem proud to come from the hood!
But listen, 
If you worked your ass off to 'start from the bottom now your up'
Fuck ya, I salute you!
But living in the hood is nothing to celebrate or be proud of like it somehow makes you 'gangster', makes you 'hard' or whatever these fucktardw say

Drake worked his ass off to be where he is
